Answer for Session3: Correlation and Linear Regression

MRC Clinical Sciences Centre (http://mrccsc.github.io/)

12/July/2016

These exercises cover the sections of Statistics in R Session3: Correlation and Linear Regression.

Exercise 1

  • Read in the file lmExercise.txt.
 lmExercise <- read.delim("../data/lmExercise.txt")
  • What is the formula for the best fit lines for X vs Y and X vs Z
 lmXY <- lm(x~y,lmExercise)
 lmXZ <- lm(x~z,lmExercise)
lmXY
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = x ~ y, data = lmExercise)
## 
## Coefficients:
## (Intercept)            y  
##    -10.7659       0.2461
 plot(x~y,lmExercise)
 abline(lmXY,col="red")

lmXZ
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = x ~ z, data = lmExercise)
## 
## Coefficients:
## (Intercept)            z  
##      6.8754      -0.4654
plot(x~z,lmExercise)
 abline(lmXZ,col="red")

  • What are the Rsquared for X vs Y and X vs Z.
